50|$|In chemistry, a <b>dangling</b> <b>bond</b> is an {{unsatisfied}} valence on an immobilized atom. An atom with a <b>dangling</b> <b>bond</b> is {{also referred}} to as an immobilized free radical or an immobilized radical, a reference to its structural and chemical similarity to a free radical.|$|E
50|$|In {{computational}} chemistry, a <b>dangling</b> <b>bond</b> generally {{represents an}} error in structure creation, in which an atom is inadvertently drawn with too few bonding partners, or a bond is mistakenly drawn with an atom at only one end.|$|E
