50|$|Some allotropes of silicon, such as {{amorphous}} silicon, {{display a}} {{high concentration of}} <b>dangling</b> <b>bonds.</b> Besides being of fundamental interest, these <b>dangling</b> <b>bonds</b> are important in modern semiconductor device operation. Hydrogen introduced to the silicon during the synthesis process is well known to replace <b>dangling</b> <b>bonds,</b> as are other elements such as oxygen.|$|R
